SIMPLE: strickle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strickle
<hw>Stric"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Strike</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An instrument to strike grain
to a level with the measure; a strike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for whetting scythes; a
rifle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>An instrument used for
smoothing the surface of a core.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Carp. & Mason.)</fld> <def>A templet; a
pattern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An instrument used in dressing flax.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strickler</ent>⟦br⟧
